2019-12-16 14:49:01	FromGitter	<bew> @manveru about https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/pull/75719 (note: I'm quite new to the world of Nix) Why does splitting output reduces the closure size? the compiled binary would still reference the compiler (then llvm etc... no?)
2019-12-16 14:50:18	FromGitter	<manveru> basically, it referenced a path like `/nix/store/...-crystal/lib/some/path/to/some.cr` in the compiled binary, which is later used for printing backtraces and such i think
2019-12-16 14:51:02	FromGitter	<manveru> since `/nix/store/...-crystal` also contains `/nix/store/...-crystal/bin/crystal`, it'd indirectly depend on the crystal binary at runtime
2019-12-16 14:51:16	FromGitter	<manveru> which in turn needs llvm to compile stuff
2019-12-16 14:52:47	FromGitter	<manveru> by splitting the derivation output, and setting `CRYSTAL_LIBRARY_PATH` to the `lib` output, we ensure that all references only point to the subdirectory at runtime, and so it won't need the crystal binary as a runtime dependency anymore
2019-12-16 14:53:54	FromGitter	<manveru> since the subdir will be another derivation like `/nix/store/...-crystal-lib`, with no paths pointing to the other one
2019-12-16 14:55:24	FromGitter	<bew> oooh ok I see, I love the idea! That's something (the dep on the whole crystal derivation) that annoyed me, so I'm happy to see this fixed!
2019-12-16 14:55:32	FromGitter	<manveru> since nix determines dependencies by looking for store paths in all files of the output
2019-12-16 14:56:07	FromGitter	<manveru> yeah, it got my deploy sizes down to a few kilobyte instead of 300 MB or so :)
2019-12-16 14:56:33	FromGitter	<manveru> well, almost, but the remaining dependencies are really tiny anyway
2019-12-16 14:57:43	FromGitter	<manveru> i'd really appreciate if you could try to build something with it, and see if it still works when errors happen, or some more complex libraries are in play
2019-12-16 14:57:45	FromGitter	<bew> you've been using Nix for a long time? I just got into it (1-2 weeks) to have my latest packages on an old distrib I have to use at work, and I think I'll move to nixos when I have time
2019-12-16 14:58:07	FromGitter	<manveru> yeah, a couple of years now
2019-12-16 14:58:26	FromGitter	<manveru> started using nixos fulltime around 2016 or so :)
2019-12-16 14:58:57	FromGitter	<bew> so nice! still using it I guess? :D
2019-12-16 14:59:04	FromGitter	<manveru> sure :D
2019-12-16 14:59:19	FromGitter	<manveru> also finally my fulltime job since september
2019-12-16 14:59:59	FromGitter	<bew> my very first derivation was to compile this year' advent of code in crystal (yes I'm proud of it 😃 )
2019-12-16 15:00:20	FromGitter	<manveru> now i'm just trying to make the crystal ecosystem for nix better, it's already pretty painless to build crystal packages using crystal2nix and such, but there's still some work to do
2019-12-16 15:01:00	FromGitter	<manveru> i'd love in particular if shard lockfiles could include a hash, so we wouldn't need crystal2nix anymore
2019-12-16 15:02:43	<--	ht_ (~Thunderbi@2a02:a210:9501:ad80:8ab:93c4:d704:6dc1) has quit (Quit: ht_)
2019-12-16 15:04:10	FromGitter	<bew> crystal2nix is a function? or a pkg?
2019-12-16 15:04:57	FromGitter	<bew> still don't understand why I would need these kind of X2nix tool
2019-12-16 15:06:50	<--	DTZUZO (~DTZUZO@S0106bcd165662a4d.vs.shawcable.net) has quit (Read error: Connection reset by peer)
2019-12-16 15:09:09	FromGitter	<manveru> it's a pretty simple script
2019-12-16 15:09:38	FromGitter	<manveru> https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/pkgs/development/compilers/crystal/crystal2nix.cr
2019-12-16 15:10:13	FromGitter	<manveru> it just runs `nix-prefetch-git` for each dependency, so we know the expected hash of it
2019-12-16 15:10:33	FromGitter	<manveru> in nix, you cannot download anything during a build, unless you know already the hash of what you expect
2019-12-16 15:11:36	FromGitter	<manveru> that ensures that builds are reproducible, can be cached, and don't have side-effects
2019-12-16 15:14:38	-->	DTZUZO (~DTZUZO@S0106bcd165662a4d.vs.shawcable.net) has joined #crystal-lang
2019-12-16 15:15:25	FromGitter	<manveru> so, if your language-specific package manager doesn't put hashes in the lockfile, we have to calculate them before starting a build
2019-12-16 15:15:43	FromGitter	<manveru> and that's what all those 2nix tools are doing
2019-12-16 15:22:21	FromGitter	<bew> okay, will have to test that some day with a bigger project, thanks for the explanation!
2019-12-16 15:22:23	<--	ur5us (~ur5us@2406:e002:6b2c:e401:159d:33a3:c47:596) has quit (Ping timeout: 245 seconds)
2019-12-16 15:27:17	FromGitter	<straight-shoota> > i'd love in particular if shard lockfiles could include a hash, so we wouldn't need crystal2nix anymore ⏎  ⏎ => https://github.com/crystal-lang/shards/issues/242
2019-12-16 15:27:33	FromGitter	<straight-shoota> Bascially just needs someone to implement it (which shouldn't be hard, really).
2019-12-16 15:28:25	-->	ur5us (~ur5us@2406:e002:6b2c:e401:159d:33a3:c47:596) has joined #crystal-lang
