2019-12-16 15:56:03	FromGitter	<bew> @manveru do you know if there is a simple way to use Nix as a toolchain to build static binaries?
2019-12-16 15:56:24	FromGitter	<manveru> yeah
2019-12-16 15:57:04	FromGitter	<manveru> you just pass `--static` to your build, and provide the static versions of your libraries in buildInputs
2019-12-16 15:57:19	FromGitter	<bew> for exemple for a crystal script, how would you go about statically build a standalone binary for it?
2019-12-16 15:57:37	FromGitter	<bew> "provide the static versions of your libraries in buildInputs" => how?
2019-12-16 15:57:44	FromGitter	<bew> need to rebuild all deps?
2019-12-16 15:57:47	FromGitter	<manveru> i did that at my previous company... but lost all code when i left :|
2019-12-16 15:58:09	FromGitter	<manveru> well, like static openssl/gmp/readline/etc...
2019-12-16 15:59:07	FromGitter	<bew> are these already in the binary cache? or do we need to enable something for all deps and rebuild them?
2019-12-16 15:59:44	FromGitter	<manveru> i can make you an example later :)
2019-12-16 16:01:26	FromGitter	<manveru> ok, updated the PR
2019-12-16 16:09:50	FromGitter	<bew> cool (may I suggest not doing force pushes, so it's easier to update local branches, or review the changes)
2019-12-16 16:19:05	FromGitter	<manveru> well, i have to squash it in the end anyway...
2019-12-16 16:19:14	FromGitter	<manveru> but yeah, sorry, old habit :|
2019-12-16 16:24:36	FromGitter	<manveru> @bew https://gist.github.com/manveru/ebe3b669fdec44f0d9b9c6f04d4986f2 there you go
2019-12-16 16:24:44	FromGitter	<manveru> static compiles made easy :)
